=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: From enantiopure N-Boc-3-hydroxymethylpiperidine, install the phthalimidomethyl group by Mitsunobu/Gabriel reaction with phthalimide to give N-Boc-(S)-3-(phthalimidomethyl)piperidine, then remove Boc to obtain (S)-3-(phthalimidomethyl)piperidine. | Step 2: Buchwald–Hartwig amination of the appropriately substituted bromo-dimethylbenzyl alcohol (the aryl bromide matching the target aryl ring, e.g. 4-bromo-2,6-dimethylbenzyl alcohol isomer for the target pattern) with (S)-3-(phthalimidomethyl)piperidine gives the aniline intermediate Ar-CH2OH where Ar = c3c(C)ccc(N1CCC[C@@H]1CH2N-phthalimide)c3C. | Step 3: Convert that benzyl alcohol to the corresponding benzyl bromide (PBr3 or MsCl then LiBr) to give Ar-CH2Br. | Step 4: Williamson ether coupling of the aza-naphthol core Cc1ccc2cccc(O)c2n1 (the target heteroaryl phenol) with Ar-CH2Br under K2CO3/Cs2CO3 gives the target Cc1ccc2cccc(OCc3c(C)ccc(N4CCC[C@@H]4CN4C(=O)c5ccccc5C4=O)c3C)c2n1.

=== NORMALIZED STUDENT ANSWER ===
Step 1: From enantiopure N-Boc-3-hydroxymethylpiperidine, install the phthalimidomethyl group by Mitsunobu/Gabriel reaction with phthalimide to give N-Boc-(S)-3-(phthalimidomethyl)piperidine, then remove Boc to obtain (S)-3-(phthalimidomethyl)piperidine. | Step 2: Buchwald–Hartwig amination of the appropriately substituted bromo-dimethylbenzyl alcohol (the aryl bromide matching the target aryl ring, e.g. 4-bromo-2,6-dimethylbenzyl alcohol isomer for the target pattern) with (S)-3-(phthalimidomethyl)piperidine gives the aniline intermediate Ar-CH2OH where Ar = c3c(C)ccc(N1CCC[C@@H]1CH2N-phthalimide)c3C. | Step 3: Convert that benzyl alcohol to the corresponding benzyl bromide (PBr3 or MsCl then LiBr) to give Ar-CH2Br. | Step 4: Williamson ether coupling of the aza-naphthol core Cc1ccc2cccc(O)c2n1 (the target heteroaryl phenol) with Ar-CH2Br under K2CO3/Cs2CO3 gives the target Cc1ccc2cccc(OCc3c(C)ccc(N4CCC[C@@H]4CN4C(=O)c5ccccc5C4=O)c3C)c2n1.

